Facebook Developer Garage Palo Alto - Roadmap Edition
Mark went
Join the Facebook team at the Facebook Developer Garage Palo Alto for a sneak peek of the Facebook Platform roadmap. Please RSVP soon to reserve your spot as spaces are limited. If you can't make the event in person, you can watch a live stream of the event here: http://developers.facebook.com/news.php?blog=1&story=325 ------- ***THIS IS AN INVITE-ONLY EVENT*** Event Details (Subject to change) 2:30 PM – 3:00 PM – Guests arrive & Registration 3:00 PM - Doors Open 3:00 PM - 3:30 PM - Registration continues/Grab a snack and a seat 3:30-4:45 PM - Facebook speaks 4:45-6:30 PM - Happy Hour Location: Facebook Headquarters 1601 S. California Ave. Palo Alto, CA 94301 ------- Transportation *By Car If you're driving, please park at 1050 Page Mill Road. Please watch for signs marked “Developer Garage” or “1601” to help direct you to the parking lot. We'll provide shuttles which will run throughout the duration of the event which will transport you to and from the event location. ****Please note, there will NOT be parking at Facebook HQ. *By Train If you're arriving by Caltrain, please arrive at the downtown Palo Alto stop (95 University Ave., Palo Alto). Go to our shuttle stop at the green loading zone along the northbound tracks in the parking lot at the end of Lytton St. We'll have shuttles there to transport you to and from the event. Please allow at least 15 minutes for transportation. Representatives will be waiting at both sites to help direct you.

Eating Contest Party
Mark went
This will be an event at our house with various eating contests (plus regular food), like: - Saltine Challenge - Taco-stravaganza: http://ywong.livejournal.com/292882.html - Funny Bunny - Pie-Eating Contest - CinnaMunch Showdown - Cheese-Puff Catching - .... more? (Original note: http://www.facebook.com/note.php?note_id=92502136831&comments ) Not everyone who attends has to participate, but non-contestants are encouraged to pledge donations to offset the food outlay. If there are enough pledges, we will award prizes too. You can also pledge money - PayPal me - if you are not coming, and we will make sure to photo/video-document whatever event(s) you want to see and post them on Facebook! If anyone has ideas for other contests, please post them in the comments! When RSVP'ing, please indicate which contest(s) you are willing to enter. We will also invite James Wang to be on hand in case anything goes wrong. Guests are welcome! Please share this event with others, especially those whom you think would be particularly good/hilarious at an eating contest!
